Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Bring a large #saucepan{} of @water{2%l} to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the linguine.

Halve the @red chilli{1/2%piece} lengthways, deseed, then finely chop. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(grated with garlic press).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @panko breadcrumbs{10%g}, @Italian style herbs{1%tsp} and half the garlic with the @water for the breadcrumbs{2%tbsp} and @salt for the breadcrumbs{1/4%tsp}, then add the @British beef mince{240%g}.

Season with @ground black pepper{} and mix together with your hands. Roll into evenly-sized balls, 5 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the meatballs onto a large #baking tray{}. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} and fry until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly.

Add the remaining garlic and fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @beef stock paste{1%tbsp}, @finely chopped tomatoes with basil{1%can}, @water for the sauce{100%ml} and @sugar for the sauce{1/2%tsp}, then cover with a #lid{} or #foil{} and simmer until the sauce has thickened, ~{6-7%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

Meanwhile, when your pan of water is boiling, add the @linguine{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

When everything is ready, pop the sauce back on medium heat to warm through, then stir in the cooked meatballs and linguine.

Sprinkle in half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Toss to coat and combine, then taste and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed.

Share the meatball linguine between your #bowls{} and sprinkle over the red chilli (careful, it's hot - add less if you'd prefer things milder) and remaining cheese.

Serve the @pea shoots{40%g} alongside and drizzle over the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} to finish. Enjoy!